# Roots of Vietnam runs on Cloudflare (D1 + Pages). Most configuration lives in
# wrangler.toml ([vars] + D1/KV/R2 bindings), NOT here:
#
#   - Secrets (JWT_SECRET):   `wrangler pages secret put JWT_SECRET`  (production)
#                             `.dev.vars` file with `JWT_SECRET=...`  (local dev)
#   - Plain vars (JWT_EXPIRES_IN, NODE_ENV, CORS_ORIGIN, COOKIE_DOMAIN): wrangler.toml
#   - Bindings (DB, KV, MEDIA): wrangler.toml
#
# This root .env only feeds the Vite frontend (vite.config.ts `envDir: '..'`).
# Both vars below are OPTIONAL — leave unset for the standard same-origin setup.

# Same-origin API: leave empty so the frontend calls /api on its own origin.
# Set to a full URL only if the API is hosted on a different origin.
VITE_API_URL=""

# Dev only: when running the Vite HMR server (`pnpm dev:web` on :5173), it
# proxies /api + /uploads here. Defaults to the `wrangler pages dev` port.
VITE_PROXY_TARGET="http://localhost:8788"
